'''beIN Media Group''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|b|iː|ɪ|n}} {{respell|BEE|in}}; {{lang-ar|مجموعة بي إن الإعلامية}}, ''Majmū‘at Bī’in al-I‘lāmiyyah'') is a Qatari sport and entertainment network founded on 1 January 2014 by [[Nasser Al-Khelaifi]], headquartered in [[Doha]], [[Qatar]]. The network [[beIN Sports]] was created in France in June 2012.
== History == [[beIN Sports]] as a brand was first launched in June 2012 in France. On 31 December 2013, Al Jazeera Sport was officially [[Corporate spin-off|spun off]] from the [[Al Jazeera Media Network]] to become beIN Sports. In October 2014, it was announced that beIN Media Group had agreed to acquire pay-TV sports channel Setanta Sports Australia, with Setanta being rebranded as [[BeIN Sports (Australia)|beIN Sports Australia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=beIn Media Group to acquire Setanta Sports Australia|url=http://www.businessandleadership.com/marketing/item/47135-bein-media-group-to-acquire|website=Business and Leadership.com}}</ref>
In 2015, [[beIN Sports]] launched a HD channel specially dedicated to football in [[Spain]]. The group declared in November 2015 that it would be expanding from sports-only programming to include entertainment and movies as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadbandtvnews.com/2015/11/02/bein-expands-dth-bouquet-for-mena/|title=BeIn expands DTH bouquet for MENA, offers Euro2016|publisher=Broadband TV News|author=Robert Briel|date=2 November 2015|accessdate=8 January 2016}}</ref>
It was announced in January 2016 that beIN Media Group secured an agreement with [[Turner Broadcasting System]], allowing it exclusive rights to broadcast a number of Turner-licensed entertainment and news channels across the Middle East and North Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/qatar-s-bein-inks-turner-deal-expand-entertainment-channels-616715.html#.Vo8FcvkrLIU|title=Qatar's beIN inks Turner deal to expand entertainment channels|publisher=Arabian Business|date=8 January 2016|accessdate=8 January 2016}}</ref>
It was rumored in November 2015 that beIN Media Group exhibited interested in purchasing [[Miramax]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2015/11/16/miramax-sale-bein-media/|title=The Studio Behind 'Pulp Fiction' Could Be Sold Soon|publisher=Fortune|author=Tom Huddleston, Jr.|date=16 November 2015|accessdate=8 January 2016}}</ref> On 1 March 2016, beIN Media Group announced its full acquisition of Miramax from [[Filmyard Holdings]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/03/business/media/miramax-is-bought-by-the-qatari-bein-media-group.html?_r=0 |title=Miramax Is Bought by the Qatari beIN Media Group |publisher=The New York Times |author=Michael Cieply |date=2 March 2016 |accessdate=10 March 2016 }}</ref>
It was announced in August 2016 that beIN Media Group acquired [[Turkey|Turkish]] pay TV service [[Digiturk]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Digiturk|url=http://www.beinsports.com/en/bein-digiturk/|website=beIN Media Group|accessdate=30 September 2016}}</ref>
