'''Don Edwards Park''' is a four field [[baseball]] complex located in [[Newark, Ohio]], built in 1963. It hosted a semi-professional league team the [[Newark Buffalos]]/Bison in 1994 and in 1995.<ref name="flhistory">[http://flhistory.gofreeserve.com/NewarkBuffaloes.htm Newark Buffalos/Bison] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090704074007/http://flhistory.gofreeserve.com/NewarkBuffaloes.htm |date=July 4, 2009 }}, URL accessed May 8, 2010.</ref> And is currently home to the [[Licking County Settlers]] of the [[Great Lakes Summer Collegiate League]].  Don Edwards Park has served as the host site for nine [[Babe Ruth League|Babe Ruth World Series]] events.  The Park has shoted a mulitiude of tournaments over the years.  The facility is currenlty owned by the [[Newark, Ohio|City of Newark]] and operated by the Licking County Family YMCA.

