{{Infobox football biography |name = Mirlind Daku |image = |image_size = |fullname = Mirlind Daku |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1998|1|1|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Gjilan]], [[Serbia and Montenegro|FR Yugoslavia]] |height = {{convert|1.92|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} |position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] |currentclub = [[NK Osijek|Osijek]] |clubnumber = |youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2017 |youthclubs1 = [[KF Hajvalia|Hajvalia]] |years1 = 2017 |clubs1 = [[KF Hajvalia|Hajvalia]] |caps1 = 14 |goals1 = 1 |years2 = 2017–2018 |clubs2 = [[KF Llapi|Llapi]] |caps2 = 44 |goals2 = 23 |years3 = 2018– |clubs3 = [[NK Osijek|Osijek]] |caps3 = 0 |goals3 = 0 |years4 = 2018– |clubs4 = → [[NK Osijek|Osijek]] II |caps4 = 2 |goals4 = 1 |nationalyears1 = 2017– |nationalteam1 = [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo U21]] |nationalcaps1 = 4 |nationalgoals1 = 0<!--Only matches as FIFA member are included.--> <!-- Don't add parameter unless he debuted with national team. |nationalyears2 = 2018– |nationalteam2 = [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] |nationalcaps2 = 0 |nationalgoals2 = 0 --> |club-update = 2 September 2018 |nationalteam-update = 7 September 2018 }} '''Mirlind Daku''' (born 1 January 1998) is a Kosovan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for Croatian club [[NK Osijek|Osijek]].
==Club career== ===Llapi=== On 24 January 2017. Daku joined [[Football Superleague of Kosovo]] side [[KF Llapi|Llapi]], on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegrafi.com/zyrtare-llapi-transferon-tre-futbolliste-foto/|title=Zyrtare: Llapi transferon tre futbollistë (Foto)|trans-title=Official: Llapi transfers three footballers|quote=Skuadra nga Podujeva ka afruar një qendërsulmues dhe dy mesfushor me tipare sulmuese si Mirlind Daku qe vjen nga Hajvalia, Qëndrim Dautaj nga Gjilani dhe Alban Mavriqi nga Drita e Gjilanit|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|language=Albanian|date=31 January 2017}}</ref>
===Osijek=== ====First team==== On 20 July 2018. Daku joined [[Croatian First Football League]] side [[NK Osijek|Osijek]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegrafi.com/daku-prezantohet-te-osijeku-hap-madh-per-mua/|title=Daku prezantohet te Osijeku: Hap i madh për mua|trans-title=Daku is presented to Osijek: Great step for me|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|language=Albanian|date=20 July 2018}}</ref> on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://futbollikosovar.com/zyrtare-daku-transferohet-te-osijek-nenshkruan-kontrate-afatgjate/20419/superliga/|title=Zyrtare: Daku transferohet te Osijek, nënshkruan kontratë afatgjate|trans-title=Official: Daku transferred to Osijek, signs a long-term contract|quote=20-vjeçari ka arritur marrëveshje me skuadrën e Osijekut dhe ka nënshkruar për 4 vite me skuadrën kroate, ka konfirmuar për Sportin në KTV, drejtori për transferime të jashtme në skuadrën e Llapit, Afrim Ajeti|website=Futbolli Kosovar|language=Albanian|date=19 July 2018}}</ref> Although signed contract with the first team, he continued to play for reserve team of Osijek.
====Reserve team==== On 25 August 2018. Daku made his debut with [[NK Osijek|Osijek]] II in a [[Croatian Second Football League]] match against [[HNK Šibenik|Šibenik]] after being named in the starting line-up. On 2 September 2018, he scored his first goal for Osijek II in a 1–0 home win against [[NK Sesvete|Sesvete]].
==International career== ===Under-21=== On 21 March 2017. Daku received a call-up from [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo U21]] for a [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group 5|2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]] match against [[Republic of Ireland national under-21 football team|Republic of Ireland U21]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/?p=17931|title=Lista e futbollistëve të Përfaqësueses U21|trans-title=List of the players of national U21 team|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=21 March 2017}}</ref> On 9 November 2017, he made his debut with Kosovo U21 in match against [[Israel national under-21 football team|Israel U21]] after coming on as a substitute at 54th minute in place of [[Ardit Gashi]].
===Senior=== On 22 January 2018. Daku received his first call-up from [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] in a [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.korneri.net/lajmi-i-fundit-lista-e-kosoves-kunder-azerbeixhanit/|title=Lajmi i fundit: Lista e Kosovës kundër Azerbajxhanit|trans-title=Breaking news: List of Kosovo versus Azerbaijan|publisher=Korneri|language=Albanian|date=22 January 2018|accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref> The match however was cancelled two days later, which prolonged his debut.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.affa.az/index.php/news/friendly-match-cancelled/61160|title=Friendly match canceled|quote=According to the results of the UEFA Nations League’s draws held in Lausanne, Switzerland today, it was defined that Azerbaijan and Kosovo national teams will compete in the same group. Thereby the match planned to be held between these teams in Antalya, Turkey on February 2 was canceled. The both football federations’ officials met after the draw ceremony and reached a mutual agreement in this regard|publisher=[[Association of Football Federations of Azerbaijan]]|date=25 January 2018}}</ref>
