{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Newtown Oval | nickname = | country = Australia | image = | location = [[Maryborough, Queensland|Maryborough]], [[Australia]] | establishment = 1922 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = 10,000 | end1 = | end2 = | club1 = [[Queensland cricket team|Queensland]] | year1 = 1994 | date = 21 October | year = 2011 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/104.html Ground profile }}
'''Newtown Oval''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Maryborough, Queensland]], [[Australia]]. The first recorded match on the ground came when Maryborough played [[Victoria cricket team|Victoria]] on [[Christmas Day]] in 1922.<ref name="OTH">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/104_misc.html|title=Other matches played on Newtown Oval, Maryborough|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=20 October 2011}}</ref> The ground later held its only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in 1994 when [[Queensland cricket team|Queensland]] played the touring [[Zimbabwe national cricket team|Zimbabweans]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/104_f.html|title=First-Class Matches played on Newtown Oval, Maryborough|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref> with the match ending in a 4 wicket victory for Queensland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/59/59886.html|title=Queensland v Zimbabweans, 1994/95|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref>
